comfort food on a rainy night
.
.
stir fry mee suah
.
swipe 🔙 to see
.
noodles are first blanched then stir fried quickly to absorb in the gravy of dried scallops, shiitake mushroom, pork belly and tofu puff with homemade chicken broth. add a tablespoon sesame oil, little sea salt and a few splash hua tiao chiew to taste. celery, fresh crunchy prawns and strip omelette lend colour to the dish which then garnished with roasted cashew nuts n homemade crispy seaweed
.
👀the last two pic are the ingredients n the brand of mee suah that i used
.
.
